The paper focuses on developing a framework for predicting video quality of experience (QoE) using deep learning techniques. This involves extracting generalized features and learning representations using neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques such as word embeddings, which suggests a possible fit with cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
